  "context_sent_to_llm": "\nDocument: ArcaUsTreasuryFund_20200207_N-2_EX-99.K5_11971930_EX-99.K5_Development Agreement.pdf\nSection: 10. Entire Agreement\u037e Governing Law\nPage: 4\n\nThis Agreement contains the entire agreement of the parties and supersedes all prior agreements, understandings and arrangements with respect to the subject matter hereof. This Agreement shall be construed in accordance with the laws of the State of New York applicable to contracts formed and to be performed entirely within the State of New York, without regard to conflict of laws principles, and in accordance with the applicable provisions of the Investment Fund Act. In such case, to the extent the applicable laws of the State of New York, or any of the provisions herein, conflict with the provisions of the Investment Fund Act, the latter shall control. [ Remainder of Page Intentionally Left Blank ]\n\n\n\nDocument: ArcaUsTreasuryFund_20200207_N-2_EX-99.K5_11971930_EX-99.K5_Development Agreement.pdf\nSection: ARCA CAPITAL MANAGEMENT, LLC\nPage: 1\n\nThis Agreement ( \"Agreement\" ) is made as of [___], 2020 by and between ARCA U.S. TREASURY FUND, a Delaware statutory trust (the \"Fund\" ), and ARCA CAPITAL MANAGEMENT, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (the \"Blockchain Administrator\" ).\n\n\n\nDocument: ArcaUsTreasuryFund_20200207_N-2_EX-99.K5_11971930_EX-99.K5_Development Agreement.pdf\nSection: 7. Duration and Termination of this Agreement\nPage: 3\n\n(a) This Agreement shall become effective as of the first date above written. This Agreement may be terminated at any time, without the payment of any penalty, upon 60 days' written notice, by the vote of a majority of the outstanding voting securities of the Fund or by the vote of the Fund's Trustees or by the Blockchain Administrator. The provisions of Section 5 of this Agreement shall remain in full force and effect, and the Blockchain Administrator shall remain entitled to the benefits thereof, notwithstanding any termination of this Agreement.\n\n\n\nDocument: ArcaUsTreasuryFund_20200207_N-2_EX-99.K5_11971930_EX-99.K5_Development Agreement.pdf\nSection: 7. Duration and Termination of this Agreement\nPage: 3\n\nFurther, notwithstanding the termination or expiration of this Agreement as aforesaid, the Blockchain Administrator shall be entitled to any amounts owed under Section 4 through the date of termination or expiration, and Section 5 shall continue in force and effect and apply to the Blockchain Administrator and its representatives as and to the extent applicable.\n\n\n\nDocument: ArcaUsTreasuryFund_20200207_N-2_EX-99.K5_11971930_EX-99.K5_Development Agreement.pdf\nSection: 7. Duration and Termination of this Agreement\nPage: 3\n\n(b)  This Agreement shall continue in effect for two years from the date hereof, and thereafter shall continue automatically for successive annual periods, provided that such continuance is specifically approved at least annually by (A) the vote of the Board, or by the vote of a majority of the outstanding voting securities of the Fund and (B) the vote of a majority of the Fund's directors who are not parties to this Agreement or \"interested persons\" (as such term is defined in Section 2(a)(19) of the Investment Fund Act) of any such party, in accordance with the requirements of the Investment Fund Act.\n\n\n\nDocument: ArcaUsTreasuryFund_20200207_N-2_EX-99.K5_11971930_EX-99.K5_Development Agreement.pdf\nSection: ARCA CAPITAL MANAGEMENT, LLC\nPage: 1\n\nWHEREAS, the Fund is a closed-end management investment fund that has registered as an investment company under the Investment Company Act of 1940, as amended (the \"Investment Company Act\" ) and that intends to operate as an interval fund pursuant to Rule 23c-3 under the Investment Company Act\u037e\n\nWHEREAS, the Fund desires to retain the Blockchain Administrator to provide services related to the development of ERC-1404 compatible digital securities and administration of the smart contracts underlying the Fund's digital securities in the manner and on the terms set forth herein\u037e\n\nWHEREAS, the Blockchain Administrator is willing to provide such services to the Fund on the terms and conditions set forth herein\u037e\n\nWHEREAS, the Blockchain Administrator will also serve as the Fund's investment adviser (the \"Adviser\" ) pursuant to an Investment Advisory Agreement entered into by and between the Fund and the Adviser (as amended from time to time, the \"Advisory Agreement\" )\u037e and\n\nWHEREAS, the Fund bears all costs and expenses incurred in its operation, administration and transactions which are not specifically assumed by the Adviser pursuant to the Advisory Agreement or this Agreement.\n",
  "generated_answer": "Based on the provided context, the agreement is between ARCA U.S. TREASURY FUND (the \"Fund\") and ARCA CAPITAL MANAGEMENT, LLC (the \"Blockchain Administrator\"). The key points of the agreement are:\n\n* The Fund is a closed-end management investment fund registered under the Investment Company Act of 1940 and intends to operate as an interval fund.\n* The Blockchain Administrator will provide services related to the development of ERC-1404 compatible digital securities and administration of the smart contracts underlying the Fund's digital securities.\n* The Blockchain Administrator will also serve as the Fund's investment adviser pursuant to an Investment Advisory Agreement.\n* The agreement has a duration of two years from the date of the agreement, and thereafter will continue automatically for successive annual periods, subject to annual approval by the Fund's Board and directors.\n* The agreement can be terminated at any time without penalty upon 60 days' written notice by the vote of a majority of the outstanding voting securities of the Fund, the Fund's Trustees, or the Blockchain Administrator.\n* Upon termination, the Blockchain Administrator will remain entitled to any amounts owed under Section 4 and the benefits of Section 5.\n* The agreement is governed by the laws of the State of New York and the applicable provisions of the Investment Fund Act.\n\nSome of the key restrictions and obligations include:\n* The Fund bears all costs and expenses incurred in its operation, administration, and transactions, except for those specifically assumed by the Adviser or the Blockchain Administrator.\n* The agreement is subject to the requirements of the Investment Fund Act and the Investment Company Act of 1940.\n* The Blockchain Administrator is entitled to the benefits of Section 5, notwithstanding any termination of the agreement.\n* The agreement supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, and arrangements with respect to the subject matter.",
