  "context_sent_to_llm": "\nDocument: ArcaUsTreasuryFund_20200207_N-2_EX-99.K5_11971930_EX-99.K5_Development Agreement.pdf\nSection: Document Summary\nPage: 1\n\n**Comprehensive Summary of the Agreement**\n\n**Parties:**\n\n* ARCA CAPITAL MANAGEMENT, LLC (the \"Blockchain Administrator\")\n* ARCA U.S. TREASURY FUND (the \"Fund\")\n\n**Core Purpose of the Agreement:**\n\nThe Blockchain Administrator will provide services related to the development of ERC-1404 compatible digital securities and administration of smart contracts for the Fund, and will also serve as the Fund's investment adviser.\n\n**Key Obligations:**\n\n* The Blockchain Administrator will:\n\t+ Provide services related to the development of ERC-1404 compatible digital securities and administration of smart contracts for the Fund.\n\t+ Serve as the Fund's investment adviser.\n\t+ Maintain confidentiality of the Agreement's terms and all business information shared between the parties.\n\t+ Comply with applicable laws and regulations.\n\t+ Maintain the Fund's records in accordance with the Investment Company Act.\n* The Fund will:\n\t+ Bear all costs and expenses not specifically assumed by the Blockchain Administrator under the Investment Advisory Agreement or this Agreement.\n\t+ Pay the Blockchain Administrator a fee of 0.20% of the Fund's average annual net assets, accrued daily and paid monthly in arrears.\n\t+ Indemnify and hold harmless the Blockchain Administrator and its affiliates from damages and expenses arising from actions taken or omitted in connection with its duties as blockchain administrator of the Fund.\n\n**Key Termination Rules:**\n\n* The agreement can be terminated by:\n\t+ A majority vote of the Fund's outstanding voting securities.\n\t+ The Fund's Trustees.\n\t+ The Blockchain Administrator with 60 days' written notice.\n* The agreement will automatically continue for two years and then annually, subject to annual approval by the Board and a majority of non-interested directors.\n\n**Additional Key Provisions:**\n\n* The Blockchain Administrator's services to the Fund are non-exclusive, allowing them to provide services to other parties.\n* The agreement acknowledges potential conflicts of interest between the Fund's stakeholders and the Blockchain Administrator's stakeholders, but does not specify any restrictions on these relationships.\n* The Blockchain Administrator is not liable for actions taken or omitted in connection with its duties as blockchain administrator of the Fund, and the Fund must indemnify and hold harmless the Blockchain Administrator and its affiliates from damages and expenses arising from such actions.\n* The laws of New York will govern this contract, which was formed and is to be performed entirely within the state.\n",
  "generated_answer": "**Summary of the Arca Development Agreement:**\n\nThe Arca development agreement is between ARCA CAPITAL MANAGEMENT, LLC (the \"Blockchain Administrator\") and ARCA U.S. TREASURY FUND (the \"Fund\"). The agreement outlines the Blockchain Administrator's services related to the development of ERC-1404 compatible digital securities and administration of smart contracts for the Fund, as well as its role as the Fund's investment adviser.\n\n**Key Obligations:**\n\n* The Blockchain Administrator will:\n\t+ Provide services related to the development of ERC-1404 compatible digital securities and administration of smart contracts for the Fund.\n\t+ Serve as the Fund's investment adviser.\n\t+ Maintain confidentiality of the Agreement's terms and all business information shared between the parties.\n\t+ Comply with applicable laws and regulations.\n\t+ Maintain the Fund's records in accordance with the Investment Company Act.\n* The Fund will:\n\t+ Bear all costs and expenses not specifically assumed by the Blockchain Administrator under the Investment Advisory Agreement or this Agreement.\n\t+ Pay the Blockchain Administrator a fee of 0.20% of the Fund's average annual net assets, accrued daily and paid monthly in arrears.\n\t+ Indemnify and hold harmless the Blockchain Administrator and its affiliates from damages and expenses arising from actions taken or omitted in connection with its duties as blockchain administrator of the Fund.\n\n**Key Termination Rules:**\n\n* The agreement can be terminated by:\n\t+ A majority vote of the Fund's outstanding voting securities.\n\t+ The Fund's Trustees.\n\t+ The Blockchain Administrator with 60 days' written notice.\n* The agreement will automatically continue for two years and then annually, subject to annual approval by the Board and a majority of non-interested directors.\n\n**Additional Key Provisions:**\n\n* The Blockchain Administrator's services to the Fund are non-exclusive, allowing them to provide services to other parties.\n* The agreement acknowledges potential conflicts of interest between the Fund's stakeholders and the Blockchain Administrator's stakeholders, but does not specify any restrictions on these relationships.\n* The Blockchain Administrator is not liable for actions taken or omitted in connection with its duties as blockchain administrator of the Fund, and the Fund must indemnify and hold harmless the Blockchain Administrator and its affiliates from damages and expenses arising from such actions.\n* The laws of New York will govern this contract, which was formed and is to be performed entirely within the state.",
