  "context_sent_to_llm": "\nDocument: beta_contract.pdf\nSection: Document Summary\nPage: 1\n\n**Comprehensive Summary of the Software Development Agreement**\n\n**Parties:**\n\n- **Developer:** DOT COM LLC (also referred to as the \"Developer\")\n- **Client:** Pelican Delivers Inc. (also referred to as the \"Client\")\n\n**Core Purpose of the Agreement:**\n\nThe Software Development Agreement outlines the terms and conditions for the performance of software design services and development between the Developer and the Client.\n\n**Key Obligations:**\n\n- **Developer Obligations:**\n  - Design, develop, and deliver the \"Pelican Delivers Application Phase 1\" and related services, work product, and documentation in accordance with the Project specifications outlined in the Statement of Work (SOW).\n  - Use best efforts to complete services and deliverables by the Final Delivery Date, making any necessary corrections or changes promptly.\n  - Provide reasonable assistance to the Client in completing the Services and producing the Deliverables.\n  - Transfer all works to the Client upon termination of the Agreement.\n- **Client Obligations:**\n  - Pay the Developer's Fees, Expenses (if any), and Bonus via wire transfer to the Developer's bank account.\n  - Perform Acceptance Tests within designated time periods to determine if Deliverables conform to the Service Order and Specifications.\n  - Provide reasonable assistance to the Developer in completing the Services and producing the Deliverables.\n  - Pay any outstanding fees upon termination of the Agreement.\n\n**Key Termination Rules:**\n\n- **Termination for Cause:** The Agreement can be terminated immediately by either party under certain conditions, including material breach, non-payment of undisputed fees, misappropriation of confidential information, or illegal activities.\n- **Termination Without Cause:** Either party may terminate this Agreement with two weeks' written notice, after which the Developer will cease providing services and the Client will pay for all services and deliverables up to the date of termination.\n- **Obligations Upon Termination:** Upon termination of the Agreement or any Statement of Work (SOW), the Client must pay any outstanding fees and the Developer will refund any non-accrued pre-paid fees. The Developer will also provide up to three (3) months of Termination Assistance Services, including knowledge transfer and data migration, at an additional cost to the Client.\n\n**Other Key Provisions:**\n\n- **Non-Exclusivity:** The parties acknowledge that this agreement does not create an exclusive business relationship, allowing the Developer to offer services to third parties and solicit other clients.\n- **Non-Disparagement Clause:** The Client and the Developer agree to refrain from making negative statements or posts about each other, their companies, employees, and affiliates online or offline.\n- **Indemnification:** The Developer agrees to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless the Client from losses, claims, liabilities, and damages arising from the Developer's material breach, gross negligence, willful misconduct, or violation of laws and regulations. The Client agrees to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless the Developer, its affiliates, and related parties from losses, claims, and damages arising from the Client's breach of this Agreement, gross negligence, or willful misconduct.\n- **Confidentiality and Non-Disclosure:** Each party acknowledges that they will receive confidential information from the other party and agrees to maintain it in confidence, using reasonable measures to protect it, and destroying or erasing all copies upon expiration or termination of the agreement.\n\n**Comprehensive Summary of the Agreement**\n\n**Parties:**\n\n* The parties involved in this agreement are not explicitly stated in the provided section. However, based on the context, it is likely that the parties are BETA Consulting and another entity (e.g., a client, contractor, or partner).\n\n**Core Purpose of the Agreement:**\n\n* The core purpose of this agreement is to outline the terms and conditions of the relationship between BETA Consulting and the other party, including the scope of work, payment terms, and termination procedures.\n\n**Key Obligations:**\n\n* The agreement does not explicitly state the key obligations of the parties. However, based on the context, it is likely that the agreement includes provisions related to:\n\t+ Scope of work and deliverables\n\t+ Payment terms and schedules\n\t+ Confidentiality and non-disclosure\n\t+ Intellectual property rights and ownership\n\t+ Liability and indemnification\n\t+ Termination procedures\n\n**Termination Rules:**\n\n* The agreement can be terminated with 90 days written notice.\n* Liability is capped at $500,000.\n* The governing law for this agreement is New York.\n\n**Additional Notes:**\n\n* The agreement does not provide a comprehensive summary of the terms and conditions. Additional sections or clauses may be included that are not mentioned in the provided section.\n* The parties should review the entire agreement to ensure that all necessary terms and conditions are included and understood.\n",
  "generated_answer": "**Document Summary:**\n\nThe document is a **Software Development Agreement** between **DOT COM LLC (Developer)** and **Pelican Delivers Inc. (Client)**.\n\n**Key Points:**\n\n* The agreement outlines the terms and conditions for the performance of software design services and development.\n* The Developer is responsible for designing, developing, and delivering the \"Pelican Delivers Application Phase 1\" and related services, work product, and documentation.\n* The Client is responsible for paying the Developer's Fees, Expenses (if any), and Bonus via wire transfer to the Developer's bank account.\n* The agreement includes provisions for termination, non-exclusivity, non-disparagement, indemnification, and confidentiality and non-disclosure.\n\n**Restrictions and Obligations:**\n\n* **Developer Obligations:**\n  - Design, develop, and deliver the \"Pelican Delivers Application Phase 1\" and related services, work product, and documentation in accordance with the Project specifications outlined in the Statement of Work (SOW).\n  - Use best efforts to complete services and deliverables by the Final Delivery Date, making any necessary corrections or changes promptly.\n  - Provide reasonable assistance to the Client in completing the Services and producing the Deliverables.\n  - Transfer all works to the Client upon termination of the Agreement.\n* **Client Obligations:**\n  - Pay the Developer's Fees, Expenses (if any), and Bonus via wire transfer to the Developer's bank account.\n  - Perform Acceptance Tests within designated time periods to determine if Deliverables conform to the Service Order and Specifications.\n  - Provide reasonable assistance to the Developer in completing the Services and producing the Deliverables.\n  - Pay any outstanding fees upon termination of the Agreement.\n\n**Termination Rules:**\n\n* **Termination for Cause:** The Agreement can be terminated immediately by either party under certain conditions, including material breach, non-payment of undisputed fees, misappropriation of confidential information, or illegal activities.\n* **Termination Without Cause:** Either party may terminate this Agreement with two weeks' written notice, after which the Developer will cease providing services and the Client will pay for all services and deliverables up to the date of termination.\n* **Obligations Upon Termination:** Upon termination of the Agreement or any Statement of Work (SOW), the Client must pay any outstanding fees and the Developer will refund any non-accrued pre-paid fees. The Developer will also provide up to three (3) months of Termination Assistance Services, including knowledge transfer and data migration, at an additional cost to the Client.",
