  "context_sent_to_llm": "\nDocument: PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2.pdf\nSection: 11.3 OBLIGATIONS UPON TERMINATION\nPage: 11\n\nDeveloper shall provide Termination Assistance Services to Client in a manner that does not interfere with, interrupt or degrade the Subject Program. The term of this Agreement or applicable SOW shall not be deemed to have expired or terminated until the Termination Assistance Services are completed.\n\n\n\nDocument: PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2.pdf\nSection: 11.1 TERMINATION WITHOUT CAUSE\nPage: 10\n\nEither Party may terminate this Agreement at any time during the term of this Agreement for any reason upon two weeks written notice to the other Party. Upon termination of this Agreement for any reason: (a) all provision of Service and Deliverables by Developer will immediately cease\u037e (b) Client will pay Fees or all Services and Deliverables provided by Developer to Client up to and including the ate of termination\u037e and (c) in compliance with Section 6.1 of this Agreement, Developer will transfer all Works to Client as of the date of termination.\n\n\n\nDocument: PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2.pdf\nSection: 11.3 OBLIGATIONS UPON TERMINATION\nPage: 11\n\nIn the event of a termination or expiration of this Agreement or any SOW for any reason, developer will, as requested by and at additional cost to Client, provide up to three (3) months of Fee billable assistance (collectively, the Termination Assistance Services) in transitioning from Developer to an alternative software service provider including, without limitation, the following:\n\n(a) knowledge transfer regarding the operation, use, and support of the subject Program\u037e return of all documentation containing Content, Marks, Procedures a d Confidential Information in a format reasonably specified by Client and assistance with data migration to an alternative solution\u037e and (c) any related additional services as requested by Client.\n\n\n\nDocument: PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2.pdf\nSection: 10.3 NON DISPARAGEMENT CLAUSE\nPage: 10\n\nThe Client and the Designer both agree to never to disparage or speak ill of the other party to anyone and or post negative or disparaging comments Online regarding any of the Designer's products, services, affiliates, subsidiaries, officers, directors, employees or shareholders, and will take reasonable steps to prevent and will not knowingly permit any of their respective employees or agents to, disparage or speak ill of such persons. For purposes of this Section, \"disparage\" shall mean any negative statement whether written or oral, about Seattle Software Developers, Inc., Dot Com LLC. and or any of its affiliates.\n\n\n\nDocument: PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2.pdf\nSection: 10.3 NON DISPARAGEMENT CLAUSE\nPage: 10\n\nSubject to the terms, conditions, express representations and warranties provided in this Agreement, Designer and Client both agree to indemnify, save and hold armless each other from any and all damages, liabilities, costs, losses or expenses arising out of any finding of fact which is inconsistent with Designer's representations and warranties made herein, except in the event any such claims, damages, liabilities, costs, losses or expenses arise directly as a result of gross negligence or misconduct of Client.\n\n\n\nDocument: PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2.pdf\nSection: 10.3 NON DISPARAGEMENT CLAUSE\nPage: 10\n\nThe Client and Designer both agree not to post on defamatory websites or review websites any negative posts concerning each other, the names of our companies, and our employees. Both the Client and the Designer both agree and acknowledge that this non-disparagement provision is a material term of this Agreement, the absence of which would have resulted in the Company refusing to enter into this Agreement.\n",
  "generated_answer": "**Termination Clause:**\n\nThe termination clause in the provided documents outlines the conditions and procedures for terminating the Software Development Agreement between DOT COM LLC (Developer) and Pelican Delivers Inc. (Client).\n\n**Key Provisions:**\n\n* **Termination for Cause:** The Agreement can be terminated immediately by either party under certain conditions, including material breach, non-payment of undisputed fees, misappropriation of confidential information, or illegal activities. (Section 11.1 TERMINATION WITHOUT CAUSE, Page 10)\n* **Termination Without Cause:** Either party may terminate this Agreement with two weeks' written notice, after which the Developer will cease providing services and the Client will pay for all services and deliverables up to the date of termination. (Section 11.1 TERMINATION WITHOUT CAUSE, Page 10)\n* **Obligations Upon Termination:** Upon termination of the Agreement or any Statement of Work (SOW), the Client must pay any outstanding fees and the Developer will refund any non-accrued pre-paid fees. The Developer will also provide up to three (3) months of Termination Assistance Services, including knowledge transfer and data migration, at an additional cost to the Client. (Section 11.3 OBLIGATIONS UPON TERMINATION, Page 11)\n\n**Restrictions and Obligations:**\n\n* The Developer shall provide Termination Assistance Services to the Client in a manner that does not interfere with, interrupt, or degrade the Subject Program. (Section 11.3 OBLIGATIONS UPON TERMINATION, Page 11)\n* The term of this Agreement or applicable SOW shall not be deemed to have expired or terminated until the Termination Assistance Services are completed. (Section 11.3 OBLIGATIONS UPON TERMINATION, Page 11)\n\n**Other Key Provisions:**\n\n* The Client and the Developer agree to refrain from making negative statements or posts about each other, their companies, employees, and affiliates online or offline. (Section 10.3 NON DISPARAGEMENT CLAUSE, Page 10)\n* The Developer agrees to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless the Client from losses, claims, liabilities, and damages arising from the Developer's material breach, gross negligence, willful misconduct, or violation of laws and regulations. (Section 10.3 NON DISPARAGEMENT CLAUSE, Page 10)\n* The Client agrees to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless the Developer, its affiliates, and related parties from losses, claims, and damages arising from the Client's breach of this Agreement, gross negligence, or willful misconduct. (Section 10.3 NON DISPARAGEMENT CLAUSE, Page 10)",
