  "context_sent_to_llm": "\nDocument: PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2.pdf\nSection: 11.3 OBLIGATIONS UPON TERMINATION\nPage: 11\n\nDeveloper shall provide Termination Assistance Services to Client in a manner that does not interfere with, interrupt or degrade the Subject Program. The term of this Agreement or applicable SOW shall not be deemed to have expired or terminated until the Termination Assistance Services are completed.\n\n\n\nDocument: PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2.pdf\nSection: 11.3 OBLIGATIONS UPON TERMINATION\nPage: 11\n\nIn the event of a termination or expiration of this Agreement or any SOW for any reason, developer will, as requested by and at additional cost to Client, provide up to three (3) months of Fee billable assistance (collectively, the Termination Assistance Services) in transitioning from Developer to an alternative software service provider including, without limitation, the following:\n\n(a) knowledge transfer regarding the operation, use, and support of the subject Program\u037e return of all documentation containing Content, Marks, Procedures a d Confidential Information in a format reasonably specified by Client and assistance with data migration to an alternative solution\u037e and (c) any related additional services as requested by Client.\n\n\n\nDocument: PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2.pdf\nSection: 11.1 TERMINATION WITHOUT CAUSE\nPage: 10\n\nEither Party may terminate this Agreement at any time during the term of this Agreement for any reason upon two weeks written notice to the other Party. Upon termination of this Agreement for any reason: (a) all provision of Service and Deliverables by Developer will immediately cease\u037e (b) Client will pay Fees or all Services and Deliverables provided by Developer to Client up to and including the ate of termination\u037e and (c) in compliance with Section 6.1 of this Agreement, Developer will transfer all Works to Client as of the date of termination.\n\n\n\nDocument: PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2.pdf\nSection: 12.6 OTHER DEFINITIONAL TERMS, TERMS OF CONSTRUCTION\nPage: 13\n\nAll covenants, terms, definition and other provisions from other agreements incorporated into this Agreement by reference will survive termination of this Agreement. References to statutes, regulations or laws, include any amendments, modifications or replacements of such statutes, regulations, or laws.\n\n\n\nDocument: PelicanDeliversInc_20200211_S-1_EX-10.3_11975895_EX-10.3_Development Agreement2.pdf\nSection: 12.6 OTHER DEFINITIONAL TERMS, TERMS OF CONSTRUCTION\nPage: 13\n\nThe words hereof, herein and hereunder and words of similar import when used in this Agreement refer to this Agreement as a whole and not to any particular provision of this Agreement. The words include, includes and including shall be deemed to be followed by the phrase without limitation. Unless the context in which used herein otherwise clearly requires, or has the inclusive meaning represented by the phrase and/or. All incorporations by reference of covenants, terms, definitions or other provisions from other agreements are incorporated into this Agreement as if such provisions were fully set forth herein, and include all necessary definitions and related provisions from such other agreements.\n",
  "generated_answer": "Based on the provided context, the termination provisions can be compared as follows:\n\n**Termination Without Cause (Section 11.1)**\n\n* Either Party may terminate this Agreement at any time during the term of this Agreement for any reason upon two weeks written notice to the other Party.\n* Upon termination of this Agreement for any reason:\n  * All provision of Service and Deliverables by Developer will immediately cease.\n  * Client will pay Fees for all Services and Deliverables provided by Developer to Client up to and including the date of termination.\n  * Developer will transfer all Works to Client as of the date of termination.\n\n**Obligations Upon Termination (Section 11.3)**\n\n* Developer shall provide Termination Assistance Services to Client in a manner that does not interfere with, interrupt or degrade the Subject Program.\n* The term of this Agreement or applicable SOW shall not be deemed to have expired or terminated until the Termination Assistance Services are completed.\n* In the event of a termination or expiration of this Agreement or any SOW for any reason, Developer will provide up to three (3) months of Fee billable assistance (collectively, the Termination Assistance Services) in transitioning from Developer to an alternative software service provider, including:\n  * Knowledge transfer regarding the operation, use, and support of the subject Program.\n  * Return of all documentation containing Content, Marks, Procedures, and Confidential Information in a format reasonably specified by Client.\n  * Assistance with data migration to an alternative solution.\n  * Any related additional services as requested by Client.\n\n**Key differences:**\n\n* Termination Without Cause (Section 11.1) allows for immediate cessation of services and transfer of works, while Obligations Upon Termination (Section 11.3) requires Developer to provide Termination Assistance Services for up to three months.\n* Termination Without Cause (Section 11.1) does not mention the provision of Termination Assistance Services, while Obligations Upon Termination (Section 11.3) requires Developer to provide such services.\n* Survival of Covenants and Provisions (Section 12.6) ensures that all incorporated provisions will continue to apply even after termination of the Agreement.\n\n**Restrictions and Obligations:**\n\n* Termination Without Cause (Section 11.1):\n  + Immediate cessation of services and transfer of works upon termination.\n  + Client must pay Fees for all Services and Deliverables provided by Developer up to and including the date of termination.\n* Obligations Upon Termination (Section 11.3):\n  + Developer must provide Termination Assistance Services for up to three months.\n  + Developer must provide knowledge transfer, return of documentation, and assistance with data migration.\n  + Developer must provide any related additional services as requested by Client.\n* Survival of Covenants and Provisions (Section 12.6):\n  + All incorporated provisions will continue to apply even after termination of the Agreement.\n  + References to statutes, regulations, or laws will include any amendments, modifications, or replacements.",
